A class implementing must assign itself to this field in its constructor.
It has not been tested yet the behavior of this field in an environment of multiple spatial dialects instantiated, and geometry columns associated, in the same application domain. Hopefully, the corresponding dialect always will be instantiated before the geometry type, but this assumption has to be analyzed in the NHibernate source code and tested in a real scenario.
This may be an ugly trick but it could be avoided if NHibernate provides more context of the IUserType instatiation. For example, providing the current NHibernate.Cfg.Settings object through a new interface method.
